After a lot of hesitation, visited this place for the first time on a freezing Saturday night. First of all, the cleanliness of the place is impeccable. During my short time or ordering and picking up, the public visiting areas were frequently cleaned. "Filled" dispenser of sanitizers and tissues is giving a sense of relief as well. The staff are also cheerful and courteous. Food - absolutely delicious and nearly authentic. The must orders are Kalamarakia and Spanakopita (starters), both gyro and bifteki pitas, and the roast Greek chicken. The grilled lamb chops were a bit more done (and slightly tough) than my medium-done liking, although the roasted potatoes as the side was heavenly. The food can be tasted best while hot, but since the place is not offering dine-in, takeout and warming up will nearly do the trick. Definitely recommend, will be back for more.

This place is sooo good. I have always had a good meal here. Only once did I have a piece of my order left out, but it was Friday during lunch and it was a big group delivery order for the office. Even then, I'd called later that evening to tell them I would stop by after work to either get a refund or the missing item, no big deal. When I stopped by, they didn't ask for the receipt and just offered a replacement meal plus a free dessert of my choice.  This is where my biggest recommendations come in. WHEN you stop by this place, try their baklava. It's a good healthy portion sliced into halves (pictured) and has such the perfect layering of flavors between the honey, dough, and nut fillings. Very difficult to tell yourself you'll save the other half for later and actually follow through!  The other recommendation is their spanakopita platter (also pictured), which, too, is a healthy portion of the popular dish, and my go-to when I stop by this place for a meal. It also includes a side of your choice.  And--speaking of sides--my final recommendation and possibly their most popular side item: their "big greek fries" (pictured with the spanakopita). There have been times where, I admit, I've ordered a box of these mouth-wateringly satisfying fries purely as a cheat meal along with ANOTHER SIDE of the SAME ITEM. No shame. They're fried to a crisp outer layer and topped with cheese and spices and get my highest recommendation at this restaurant.  Great service, phenomenal food, excellent theme, and fair portions make this place a must for anyone who's into Greek cuisine.  Oh and also... $5 gyros every Wednesday.

I don't get the fuss around the Greek cafe in Downtown DC. This is just as good of an establishment. The avogolemono soup is equal parts sour and savory, just as it was intended to be. The pita here is made in house and generally fantastic. The Greek burger is the most delectable hunk of meat in between two pieces of bread with feta. Its simplicity paired with superior quality cannot be beat. The staff is prompt and expedient, which is a must when you deal with a lunch crowd as large as this place's. The sides and good stuff are given a fair bit of attention. Almost all Greek places feature Greek fries, but this place unequivocally smothers those fries with melted feta and herbs. The Greek coffee could use a bit more care and attention, but the baklava definitely makes up for that. I'd skip the fad fever and just go here.
